By working with your vendor, you can then work to design an approach that combines both zero trust and SASE to keep your data as safe as it can be, regardless of where your employees work

A5. SASE focuses on managing all aspects of the technology. Enterprises wanting to implement the ZT principles should use a SASE suite to ensure that their tech secures the way people work today.

#STinsights @CIOStraightTalk #OneHCL

A4. Identity's role in a Zero Trust context is about ensuring the right people get the right level of access to the right services in the right context - and with the least amount of friction. Here is an illustration from Okta. https://t.co/TCeUP3h1Wy

A3. 1.Identify-creates an inventory, classifies them & sets baselines 
2.Protect-authentication and authorization with ZT
3. Detect‚Äîidentifies anomalies by continuously monitoring 
4. Respond-Handles threat containment & mitigation real-time

#STinsights @CIOStraightTalk #OneHCL

@ATTBusiness A7: Edge is part of the modern data architecture.  Enterprises need to make plans to prepare for the challenges and capture the opportunities. #CyberSecurity #edgecomputing #ATTInfluencer https://t.co/gKjdRVDOeg

@ATTBusiness A6: Improve security oversight by extending security operations center visibility into edge locations and telemetry. Reduce the attack surface by mandating a security policy that requires turning off unused network connectivity. #CyberSecurity #edgecomputing #ATTInfluencer

@ATTBusiness A6: Improve security protection by extending enterprise patching processes to edge systems where possible, designing compensating controls when devices cannot be patched. #CyberSecurity #edgecomputing #ATTInfluencer

@ATTBusiness A6: Discover and identify all devices connecting to the edge network by monitoring connectivity. Implement a governance policy that places all unknown devices into quarantine. #edgecomputing #cybersecurity #ATTInfluencer

@ATTBusiness A6: Segment the edge network, and restrict communications to/from edge locations by using firewalling capabilities with in-line threat-detection capabilities. #ATTInfluencer #CyberSecurity #edgecomputing
@CyberLanowitz @ATTBusiness Well said Theresa.  Visibility must be the cornerstone of any edge security strategy. #CyberSecurity

@ATTBusiness A4: There are 4 types of #cybersecurity risk associated with #edgecomputing: Malicious Hardware/Software Injections; Physical Tampering & Attacks Risk; Routing Information Attacks and Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) Attacks. #ATTInfluencer

@ATTBusiness A3: Autonomous car can process sensor data that allow it to recognize and self-pilot around pedestrians, other cars on the road, emergency roadside signage and potentially hazardous moving objects. This sensor data is processed with pre-loaded mapping data and GPS connectivity

@ATTBusiness A3: By processing data closer to the source and prioritizing traffic, #edgecomputing reduces the amount of data flowing to and from the primary network, leading to lower latency and faster overall speed. Physical distance is critical to performance. #cybersecurity #ATTInfluencer

@ATTBusiness A7. Make cybersecurity part of strategic planning process. Review where security and safety governance is currently performed, identify gaps, overlaps or opportunities for better alignment across IT, OT, supply chain and customer-facing CPS.

@ATTBusiness A5. To build better resilience, organization needs to Implement work-from-home capabilities; Adopt artificial intelligence (AI), robotics, and data and analytics to adapt supply chains and manufacturing processes and Deploy new mobile apps to interact with customers.
